prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} finished experimental editorial poster in the "cyan-grain-macro-megatype-poster-style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these literal style rules:
- Composition: place a large hard-edged saturated cyan rectangle inside a broad clean white border. Put compact condensed technical metadata near the upper-left white margin, one monumental white display word across the upper third of the cyan field, one radically enlarged macro photographic hero rising from the lower area and crossing the letters, a rough lowercase footer word at lower-left, and tiny catalog metadata at lower-right. Preserve abundant open field and use no extra scene objects.
- Subject and perspective: photograph exactly one hero extremely close from a low-side or three-quarter angle so it is cropped by the bottom and side edges and becomes a tactile abstract mass while one defining feature stays recognizable. The subject must cover selected portions of the headline but not destroy word recognition.
- Typography: use a tall ultra-condensed geometric sans-serif for the short uppercase white headline, a narrow techno-condensed sans for the upper-left label, distressed lowercase letterpress type for one footer word, and tiny monospaced metadata. Keep all visible words brief, correctly spelled, flat-printed, and free of outlines or shadows.
- Color: use warm paper white, vivid cyan-to-sky-blue, pure white type, tiny deep-marine registration marks, and one contrasting natural material family from the subject. Keep the palette strict and avoid multicolor decoration.
- Texture and lighting: use bright diffuse studio light with soft high-side direction, readable surface detail, lifted midtones, matte paper fibers, fine dry-ink grain, faint scratches, and mild photocopy wear. Keep the finish tactile but clean, with no heavy degradation.
- Graphic elements: use only the cyan inset field, three or four tiny bracket or dash marks, fragmented letter apertures caused by overlap, and minimal corner metadata. No stickers, price bursts, frames inside frames, or decorative illustrations.

Avoid: hamster, guinea pig, rodent, tan-and-white small pet, source pose, HUG, simplicity, 2025, 12mm, source numbering, creator credit, signature, logo, trademark, watermark, username, QR code, platform UI, second hero, crowd, scenic environment, dense collage, promotional badge, gradient, glossy 3D render, vector illustration, cinematic light, lens flare, neon, long copy, illegible text, malformed subject anatomy, excessive noise, heavy scratches, glitch, blur, or compression artifacts.

Important content rule: match the style fidelity anchors first, then replace the source content completely. Use the specified new subject, material detail, gesture, word, metadata, and accent mark while preserving the sparse macro-photography and monumental-type system.
